"It is avascular and lacks nerve supply"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe infrapatellar fat pad, also known as Hoffa\u0027s fat pad, is a structure located in the knee joint. It plays a role in cushioning and protecting the knee joint during movement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe correct statement is that the infrapatellar fat pad is \u003Cstrong\u003Eintracapsular and richly innervated\u003C/strong\u003E. This means it is located within the knee joint capsule and has a rich nerve supply, which can make it a source of pain if inflamed or irritated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is located outside the knee joint capsule\u003C/strong\u003E - The infrapatellar fat pad is actually located within the joint capsule\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is avascular and lacks nerve supply\u003C/strong\u003E - The fat pad is well-vascularised and innervated\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is a common site for osteoarthritis\u003C/strong\u003E - Osteoarthritis typically affects the cartilage, not the fat pad\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is primarily composed of fibrous tissue\u003C/strong\u003E - The fat pad is primarily composed of adipose tissue\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInflammation of the infrapatellar fat pad can lead to a condition known as Hoffa\u0027s syndrome, which is characterised by pain and swelling in the anterior knee.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The infrapatellar fat pad is located within the knee joint capsule.","The infrapatellar fat pad is a source of pain due to its rich nerve supply.","The infrapatellar fat pad can become inflamed, leading to a condition known as Hoffa\u0027s syndrome."],"references":